  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240°C/ 220°C (fan)/ 475°F/ Gas 9</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably an oven-proof casserole dish) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped aubergine</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tortiglioni pasta</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortiglioni </strong>and reserve a cup of the<strong> starchy cooking water</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-3.2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-3.2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-3.2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-3.2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-3.2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and cook for 5-6 min further or until starting to thicken</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1260.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
